      <item>
        <title>setting up mail server on ubuntu using postfix</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;lets install the things we need for mailing&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-console&quot; data-lang=&quot;console&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;go&quot;&gt;sudo apt-get install postfix mailutils courier-pop courier-imap&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;don’t forget to open necessary ports if you running on amazon (25, 143, POP, IMAP)
also you need to make sure that you created MX-record &lt;/p&gt;
</description>
